I was looking for a place for breakfast before I started my trek over the Brooklyn Bridge into Manhattan.  I came across the Brooklyn Bridge Bistro.  It’s conveniently located at the foot of the Bridge on the Brooklyn side.  The decor is very nice and different.  Now, the waitress was very sweet and kind.  I ordered eggs over easy and home fries with chorizo.  It took awhile for a simple plate as such to come out.  The eggs came out over well done.  And the chorizo was cold and a bit tough.  The home fries were pretty good and my white toast was a tad hard.  For the price you pay and the amount of food you get, doesn’t seem like a good deal.  But I will say the OJ was ice cold and pretty good.  I can’t speak about anything else on the menu, but I can think of a lot of other places in downtown Brooklyn for a much better breakfast.  It was ok, but not for what you pay for.
